  Vee(A) = Vee(A,A) + Vee(A,A')/2
         = Two-Electron Interaction Energy of Atom A with Itself Plus Half of Two-Electron Interaction Energy
           Between Atom A and Other Atoms of Molecule
  Vnn(A,Mol)/2 = Vnn(A,A')/2 = Half of Repulsion Energy Between Nucleus of Atom A and Other Nuclei of Molecule
  VeeC(A) = Coulomb Part of Vee(A)
  VeeX(A) = Exchange-Correlation Part of Vee(A)
